Elaine    La Roche   AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 22 board members in 3 different organizations across 5 different industries.See Board Relationships67$186,998
Background*
Ms. Elaine La Roche has been a Senior Advisor/Senior Counsel to China International Capital Corporation U.S. since March 2011. Ms. La Roche has more than 30 years' experience as a Financial Services Executive and has extensive financial expertise, business acumen and operational oversight skills. she focused on the Asian markets, specifically with regard to China, where she worked for various stretches of time over the last 18 years. Ms. La Roche served as the Chief ... Executive Officer of Salisbury Pharmacy Group. From 1997 to June 2000, she served as the Chief Executive Officer of China International Capital Corporation in Beijing. She worked at Morgan Stanley from May 1978 to June 2000, including as its Managing Director since 1987 and Chief of Staff to the Chairman and President from May 1998 to June 2000. She also served as Associate and Head of the Asia Desk at Morgan Stanley. She served as the Chief Financial Executive of Cantor Fitzgerald. Ms. La Roche served as the Chairperson of MNC Media Investment Ltd (alternate name, Linktone Ltd) from 2004 to April 21, 2008. From 2008 to 2010, Ms. La Roche was with JPMorgan Chase & Co. in Beijing, where she served as Vice Chairman, J.P. Morgan China Securities. She serves as a Board Director of Peony Capital Limited. She has been an Independent Director of Marsh & McLennan Companies, Inc. since January 18, 2012. She has been an Independent Director at Harsco Corporation since 2014. She served as an Independent Non-Executive Director of China Construction Bank Corporation from September 28, 2012 to January 5, 2016 and served the same position from June 6, 2005 to June 10, 2011. She has membership on other public company boards, including a non-U.S. company board. Ms. La Roche served as a Director of MNC Media Investment Ltd from February 2004 to April 21, 2008. She served as Independent Non-Executive Director of China Construction Bank Corporation, Singapore Branch until December 31, 2015. She served as a Director at J.P. Morgan (China) Securities. She was a Visiting Professor in the International M.B.A. and Executive M.B.A. programs at Beijing University. Ms. La Roche holds an M.B.A. in Finance from the American University and a Bachelor’s degree in International Affairs from Georgetown University School of Foreign Service.Read Full Background









